row, a low-pressure trough, which is less active, also uses this edge of the high pressure to move from Finland and goes over Estonia to the southeast, bringing light rain to Northern Estonia. On Tuesday, the low-pressure trough moves away to Russia and the high pressure takes over the Baltic Sea countries, however, there is also moisture here and in autumn, high pressure does not always mean sunshine. At night, the cloudiness is variable and it rains occasionally on the coastal areas, the wind is from the west two to seven, gusts on the coast eleven meters per second. The air temperature is minus two to plus three, on the coast occasionally five degrees. The morning is mostly cloudy, but clearer skies are in Southeast Estonia. It mainly rains on the coastal areas and the southwest and west wind blows three to eight, gusts twelve meters per second. In addition to the north coast, the northwest wind seven to twelve, gusts sixteen meters per second. In the morning, the temperature may drop below zero in some places and minus one to plus five is expected, on the coast up to eight degrees. During the day, it occasionally rains a little and the chance of rain decreases in the afternoon. The southwest and west wind blows five to eleven, gusts fifteen meters per second, there are five to ten degrees of heat. Tuesday promises to be clearer, but Wednesday will be a bit rainier. Similarly, the week continues. The air temperature is lower compared to the end of the week and stays between zero and four at night and during the day five to seven degrees are expected. The days are getting shorter and the cold is slowly creeping in, have a nice evening. Americans stood in long voting lines and the mood could be kept up by dancing, for example, a voting dance performed by a ninety-year-old lady was captured on a phone camera near a Philadelphia polling station. Have a peaceful evening to you.
